            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">This collection describes the service related experiences and military combat of Frank Joseph Niedermayer during World War II. The collection contains video oral history interview, service records, photographs, and military publications. The materials, which date mainly from 1943 thru 1947, provide evidence of American troop training, deployment, and combat activity, as well as U.S. military moral and courage.</abstract>
